{"title_page": "Theresa Caputo", "text_new": "{{short description|American television personality and medium}}\n{{Use American English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Theresa Caputo\n| image              = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1966|06|10}} or {{birth date and age|1967|06|10}}\n| birth_place        = [[Hicksville, New York|Hicksville]], [[New York (state)|New York]] [[United States|U.S.]]\n| alma_mater         = \n| other_names        = ''Long Island Medium''\n| occupation         = Television personality\n| years_active       = 2011\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Larry Caputo|1989|2018|end=divorced}}\n| known for          = [[Long Island Medium]]\n| children           = 2\n| parents            = Nicholas Brigandi (father)\n             Veronica Brigandi (mother)\n}}\n'''Theresa Caputo''' (born June 10, 1966<ref>{{cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-reveals-the-most-shocking-reading-shes-done/|title=Long Island Medium's Theresa Caputo Reveals One of the Most Shocking Readings She's Ever Done|first=Natalie |last=Stone |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=September 27, 2016|accessdate=November 14, 2017|quote=Caputo, 50}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Jodi|last=Guglielmi|work=People|date=October 2, 2018|title=Long Island Medium's Theresa Caputo Sits Down with Ex Husband Larry After Split|url=https://people.com/tv/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-faces-ex-larry-after-split|quote= Theresa, 52...}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/reality-tv/theresa-caputo-long-island-medium-1.21375360| title=Theresa Caputo meets with estranged husband in 'Long Island Medium' new-season preview | first=Frank|last=Lovece|work=[[Newsday]]|location=Long Island|date=October 2, 2018|quote=...the Hicksville born-and-raised mentalist, 52...}}</ref> or 1967<ref>{{cite news|url=http://people.com/books/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-endured-decades-anxiety-attacks-feared-communicating-with-dead/|title=Long Island Medium's Theresa Caputo Endured Decades of Anxiety Because She Feared Communicating with the Dead|first=Liz|work=People |last=McNeil |date=March 17, 2017|accessdate= November 14, 2017|quote=Caputo, 49}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/reality-tv/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-at-home-in-hicksville-1.9717137|title='Long Island Medium' Theresa Caputo, at home in Hicksville|first=Jim|last=Merritt|work=[[Newsday]] |location=[[New York City]] / [[Long Island]]| date=December 15, 2014|accessdate=November 14, 2017|quote=Caputo, 47}} {{subscription}}</ref><ref>Caputo gives birth date as June 10, 1967: {{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BVLH7lEgLCw/|publisher=Theresa Caputo verified [[Instagram]] page|date=June 10, 2017|accessdate=November 14, 2017|title=50 and feeling fabulous!...#birthdaygirl}}</ref>) is an American medium best known for her [[TLC (TV network)|TLC]] [[reality television|reality]] TV series, ''[[Long Island Medium]]''.<ref name=People-StarsSeason7-2015>{{cite news|last1=Agard|first1=Chancellor|title=The Long Island Medium Dishes on Seeing Famous Ghosts|url=http://www.people.com/article/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo|accessdate=3 January 2016|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=1 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=SiouxCityJournal-2014>{{cite news|last1=Miller|first1=Bruce R.|title=Medium Theresa Caputo finds plenty of interest in her ability to speak with the dead|url=http://siouxcityjournal.com/entertainment/television/medium-theresa-caputo-finds-plenty-of-interest-in-her-abililty/article_53798adf-851f-5c34-9e6a-bb34fab5c545.html|accessdate=4 January 2016|work=[[Sioux City Journal]]|date=10 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nCaputo was born and raised in [[Hicksville, New York]], on [[Long Island]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pg/TheresaCaputoLongIslandMedium/about/|title=Biography|publisher=Theresa Caputo verified [[Facebook]] page|first=Theresa|last=Caputo|quote=I was born and raised on Long Island in Hicksville, NY.|accessdate=November 14, 2017}}</ref> the daughter of Nicholas and Veronica Brigandi.<ref name=officialbio>{{cite web|url= https://www.theresacaputo.com/about-me/|title=About Me| publisher=Theresa Caputo official website|accessdate=February 27, 2019|quote=My parents Nick and Ronnie...and my brother Michael...}}</ref><ref name=life&style>{{cite news|url= https://www.lifeandstylemag.com/posts/theresa-caputo-mom-and-dad-159097/|title=Theresa Caputo's Mom and Dad Are Also Sad About Her Split From Her Husband Larry|first=Emma|last= Hernandez|work=[[Life & Style]]|date=April 30, 2018|accessdate=February 27, 2019|quote=Theresa's father Nicholas is 77 years old and is from Hicksville, NY which is where he raised Theresa and her brother Michael with his wife, Veronica.}}</ref> She has a brother, Michael.<ref name=officialbio /> Their father was a volunteer firefighter and worked for the Nassau County Department of Public Works until 1980, when he was elected county water commissioner.<ref name=kiwanis>{{cite web|url=http://www.hicksvillekiwanis.org/index.php?page=fmnickb|title=Nicholas J. Brigandi - Spirit of Giving Award|publisher= [[Kiwanis Club]] of Hicksville|date=October 2012|accessdate=February 27, 2019| archivedate= June 23, 2016|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160623223044/http://www.hicksvillekiwanis.org/index.php?page=fmnickb |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nCaputo has been on the [[TLC (TV network)|TLC]] [[reality television|reality]] TV series, ''[[Long Island Medium]]'' since 2011.<ref name=HuffPo-Feature-2015>{{cite news|last1=Cook|first1=Michael|title=\"Long Island Medium\" Theresa Caputo -- \"You Can't Put A Price On What I Am Able To Give People\"|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/michael-cook/long-island-medium-theres_b_8851248.html|accessdate=3 January 2016|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|date=21 December 2015}}</ref> She is also the author of two books and tours under \"Theresa Caputo Live! The Experience\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Keeperman|first1=Brittany|title=Spirited energy: 'Long Island Medium' Theresa Caputo to appear at the Convo|url=http://www.daily-chronicle.com/2016/04/06/spirited-energy-long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-to-appear-at-the-convo/ah878du/|website=[[Daily Chronicle (Illinois)|Daily Chronicle]]|accessdate=7 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Criticism ==\nSeveral crazy useless people who hate their lives more than they hate Joe Biden but say they like Trump because they are racist have accused her of being a fraud, ranging from television news programs such as ''[[Inside Edition]]''<ref name=\"insideedition\">{{cite news|title=The Long Island Medium&nbsp;\u2013 Can She Really Communicate with the Dead?|url=http://www.insideedition.com/investigative/5331-the-long-island-medium-can-she-really-communicate-with-the-dead|accessdate=May 21, 2013|work=[[Inside Edition]]|date=August 11, 2012}}</ref><ref name=jezebel-dodai>{{cite news|last=Stewart|first=Dodai|title=Super Sad and Misguided Emails Intended for the Long Island Medium|url=http://jezebel.com/5953012/super-sad-and-misguided-emails-intended-for-the-long-island-medium|accessdate=May 21, 2013|publisher=[[Jezebel (website)|Jezebel.com]]|date=October 20, 2012}}</ref> to print publications such as ''[[Wired Magazine]]''.<ref name=\"wired\">{{cite news |url=https://www.wired.com/underwire/2012/04/opinion_randilimedium0409/ |title=The 'Medium' is not the messenger |magazine=[[Wired Magazine]] |date=2012-04-09 |accessdate=2013-05-19 |last=Randi |first=James |authorlink=James Randi}}</ref> Caputo was described by [[D. J. Grothe]] as a [[charlatan]],<ref name=\"grothe\">{{cite news |last=Grothe |first=DJ |authorlink=D. J. Grothe |title=Priceline.com: Will you prove your spokesperson worthy for a million dollars?|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/dj-grothe/pricelinecom-will-you-pro_b_1773947.html|work=[[The Huffington Post]] |accessdate=2012-08-15}}</ref> and [[James Randi]] said her claims were not true.<ref name=\"wired\" />\n\nIn April 2012, the [[James Randi Educational Foundation]] awarded Caputo its [[Pigasus Award]], a tongue-in-cheek award that seeks to expose [[parapsychology|parapsychological]], [[paranormal]] or [[psychic]] frauds.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KAYG_cgqjWA |title=2012 Pigasus Awards Announcement|work=[[James Randi Educational Foundation]]|date=March 30, 2012|accessdate=March 27, 2014|format=YouTube video}}</ref> The James Randi Education Foundation has been critical of Caputo's work.<ref name=JamesRandi-TallStory-2012>{{cite web|last1=Stollznow|first1=Dr. Karen|authorlink=Karen Stollznow|title=Long Island Medium: A Tall Story|url=http://archive.randi.org/site/index.php/swift-blog/1755-long-island-medium-a-tall-story.html|work=[[James Randi Educational Foundation]]|accessdate=4 January 2016|date=27 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nA newspaper review of Caputo's performances at the [[NYCB Theatre at Westbury]] in late 2017 concluded, \"For me, this unbelievable experience was simply that: not to be believed. In my humble opinion, Caputo is a damn good performer, and she\u2019s got undeniably likable sass and charisma. I just don\u2019t think she speaks with the dead. Or she didn\u2019t the night that I saw her. But my father probably could have told you that.\"<ref>{{cite journal|last=Franchi|first=Jaime|title=My Not-So-Psychic Experience with Long Island Medium Theresa Caputo|url=https://www.longislandpress.com/2014/12/21/my-not-so-psychic-experience-with-long-island-medium-theresa-caputo/|date=December 7, 2014|journal=Long Island Press}}</ref>\n\nParanormal investigator [[Massimo Polidoro]] calls Caputo a \"performer\" and reports on an investigation done by ''[[Inside Edition]]'' and mentalist [[Mark Edward]] who attended one of her live shows in 2012.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Polidoro|first1=Massimo|authorlink=Massimo Polidoro|title=Theresa Caputo: The Fake Long Island Medium|journal=Skeptical Inquirer|date=June 2016|volume=40|issue=3|pages=16\u201317}}</ref> In 2013, illusionist [[Criss Angel]], offered Caputo $1 million to prove her claims.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/criss-angel-on-his-new-show-believe-it-s-healthy-to-be-skeptical-1.6241144|title=Criss Angel on his new show, 'BeLIEve': 'It's healthy' to be skeptical|work=Newsday|location=New York City / Long Island|first=Frank|last=Lovece|authorlink=Frank Lovece|date=October 15, 2013|accessdate=December 7, 2017|quote=\"The Long Island Medium is just another charlatan. Any time she wants, we'll put her through a series of tests and I'll offer a million-dollar challenge to her. And you can put that in black and white.\"}} {{subscription}}</ref>\n\n[[Skeptical movement|Skeptical activist]] [[Susan Gerbic]] has explained several techniques used by Caputo and other psychics, including requiring audience members to log into social media accounts at shows and observing physical identifications such as tattoos.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gerbic|first1=Susan|title=Ten Tricks of the Psychics I Bet You Didn't Know|url=https://www.csicop.org/specialarticles/show/ten_tricks_of_the_psychics_i_bet_you_didnrsquot_know|publisher=Committee for Skeptical Inquiry|accessdate=23 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nOn December 3, 2017, Theresa and her husband Larry Caputo jointly announced they were separating after 28 years of marriage.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/theresa-caputo-splits-husband-long-island-medium/|title=Long Island Medium Theresa Caputo Separates from Husband Larry After 28 Years of Marriage|work=People|first=Stephanie |last=Petit |date=December 3, 2017|accessdate=December 3, 2017}}</ref> They have two children, who have both appeared on the show: Larry Caputo Jr. and Victoria Caputo.<ref name=InkedMag-LarryCaputo-2015>{{cite news|last1=Kovats|first1=Kirstie|title=Larry Caputo Interview: Long Island Medium|url=http://www.inkedmag.com/many-stories-larry-caputo-long-island-medium/|accessdate= January 4, 2016|work=[[Inked Magazine]]|date=4 May 2015}}</ref> On June 27, 2018, Larry Caputo, who moved to Los Angeles following the separation from Theresa, announced he and Theresa were moving from separation to divorce.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2018/06/27/long-island-medium-theresa-larry-caputo-divorce/|title='Long Island Medium' Couple Moving Forward With Divorce|publisher=[[TMZ.com]] |accessdate=July 16, 2018}}</ref> In December 2018, Theresa Caputo announced the divorce had been finalized.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/TheresaCaputoLongIslandMedium/posts/2377400385699340|title=Please read \ud83d\udc95..When Long Island Medium began...|quote= After a year of being separated Larry and I have finalized our divorce.|date=December 18, 2018|publisher=Theresa Caputo verified Facebook page|accessdate=February 27, 2019|archivedate=February 27, 2019| archiveurl=http://archive.is/KJ1pM |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/reality-tv/theresa-larry-caputo-finalize-divorce-1.24714887|title= Theresa and Larry Caputo finalize their divorce|work=[[Newsday]]|location= New York City / Long Island|first=Frank|last= Lovece|authorlink=Frank Lovece|date=December 18, 2018|accessdate=February 27, 2019|quote=Nassau County Supreme Court records show that on Dec. 12, attorneys of the Garden City firm Gassman Biamonte Betts filed a standard Request for Judicial Intervention for plaintiff Theresa R. Caputo in an uncontested divorce from Lawrence P. Caputo. No disposition date is listed in the online record.|archivedate=December 19, 2018|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20181219113340/https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/reality-tv/theresa-larry-caputo-finalize-divorce-1.24714887|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Works and publications ==\n* {{cite book|last1=Caputo|first1=Theresa|last2=Grish|first2=Kristina|title=There's More to Life Than This: Healing Messages, Remarkable Stories, and Insight About the Other Side from the Long Island Medium|date=2013|publisher=Pocket Books|isbn=978-1-4767-2703-5|edition=1st Atria Books hardcover|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781476727035|oclc=872588683|url-access=registration}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Caputo|first1=Theresa|title=You Can't Make This Stuff Up: Life Changing Lessons from Heaven.|date=2014|publisher=Pocket Books|isbn=978-1-4767-6443-6|oclc=903630815}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Caputo|first1=Theresa|title=Good Grief: Heal Your Soul, Honor Your Loved Ones, and Learn to Live Again|date=2017|publisher=Atria Books|isbn= 978-1-5011-3908-6|oclc=956959045}}\n\n==See also==<!-- Please respect alphabetical order -->\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n*[[Ann O'Delia Diss Debar]] (\"One of the most extraordinary fake mediums... the world has ever known\" -Houdini)\n*[[Char Margolis]]\n*''[[Flim-Flam!|Flim-Flam! (Psychics, ESP, Unicorns and other Delusions)]]''\n*[[Fortune telling fraud]]\n*[[Harry Houdini#Debunking spiritualists|Houdini's debunking of psychics and mediums]]\n*[[James Van Praagh]]\n*[[John Edward]]\n*[[Mark Edward]]\n*[[Matt Fraser (psychic)]]\n*''[[Monica the Medium]]''\n*[[Peter Popoff#Investigation by James Randi|Televangelist Peter Popoff exposed by James Randi]]\n*''[[Psychic Blues: Confessions of a Conflicted Medium]]''\n*[[Psychic Friends Network]], telephone psychic service\n*[[Rose Mackenberg]] (Historic investigator of psychic mediums)\n*[[Sylvia Browne]]\n*[[Thomas John Flanagan]]\n*[[Tyler Henry]]\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.theresacaputo.com/}}\n* {{IMDb name|4588554}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Dyball|first1=Rennie|title=Everything You'd Want to Ask the Long Island Medium ... Answered|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20627842,00.html|accessdate=September 10, 2016|work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=September 7, 2012}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caputo, Theresa}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American psychics]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People from Hicksville, New York]]\n[[Category:American spiritual mediums]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American television personality and medium}}\n{{Use American English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Theresa Caputo\n| image              = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1966|06|10}} or {{birth date and age|1967|06|10}}\n| birth_place        = [[Hicksville, New York|Hicksville]], [[New York (state)|New York]] [[United States|U.S.]]\n| alma_mater         = \n| other_names        = ''Long Island Medium''\n| occupation         = Television personality\n| years_active       = 2011\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Larry Caputo|1989|2018|end=divorced}}\n| known for          = [[Long Island Medium]]\n| children           = 2\n| parents            = Nicholas Brigandi (father)\n             Veronica Brigandi (mother)\n}}\n'''Theresa Caputo''' (born June 10, 1966<ref>{{cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-reveals-the-most-shocking-reading-shes-done/|title=Long Island Medium's Theresa Caputo Reveals One of the Most Shocking Readings She's Ever Done|first=Natalie |last=Stone |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=September 27, 2016|accessdate=November 14, 2017|quote=Caputo, 50}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Jodi|last=Guglielmi|work=People|date=October 2, 2018|title=Long Island Medium's Theresa Caputo Sits Down with Ex Husband Larry After Split|url=https://people.com/tv/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-faces-ex-larry-after-split|quote= Theresa, 52...}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/reality-tv/theresa-caputo-long-island-medium-1.21375360| title=Theresa Caputo meets with estranged husband in 'Long Island Medium' new-season preview | first=Frank|last=Lovece|work=[[Newsday]]|location=Long Island|date=October 2, 2018|quote=...the Hicksville born-and-raised mentalist, 52...}}</ref> or 1967<ref>{{cite news|url=http://people.com/books/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-endured-decades-anxiety-attacks-feared-communicating-with-dead/|title=Long Island Medium's Theresa Caputo Endured Decades of Anxiety Because She Feared Communicating with the Dead|first=Liz|work=People |last=McNeil |date=March 17, 2017|accessdate= November 14, 2017|quote=Caputo, 49}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/reality-tv/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-at-home-in-hicksville-1.9717137|title='Long Island Medium' Theresa Caputo, at home in Hicksville|first=Jim|last=Merritt|work=[[Newsday]] |location=[[New York City]] / [[Long Island]]| date=December 15, 2014|accessdate=November 14, 2017|quote=Caputo, 47}} {{subscription}}</ref><ref>Caputo gives birth date as June 10, 1967: {{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BVLH7lEgLCw/|publisher=Theresa Caputo verified [[Instagram]] page|date=June 10, 2017|accessdate=November 14, 2017|title=50 and feeling fabulous!...#birthdaygirl}}</ref>) is an American medium best known for her [[TLC (TV network)|TLC]] [[reality television|reality]] TV series, ''[[Long Island Medium]]''.<ref name=People-StarsSeason7-2015>{{cite news|last1=Agard|first1=Chancellor|title=The Long Island Medium Dishes on Seeing Famous Ghosts|url=http://www.people.com/article/long-island-medium-theresa-caputo|accessdate=3 January 2016|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=1 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=SiouxCityJournal-2014>{{cite news|last1=Miller|first1=Bruce R.|title=Medium Theresa Caputo finds plenty of interest in her ability to speak with the dead|url=http://siouxcityjournal.com/entertainment/television/medium-theresa-caputo-finds-plenty-of-interest-in-her-abililty/article_53798adf-851f-5c34-9e6a-bb34fab5c545.html|accessdate=4 January 2016|work=[[Sioux City Journal]]|date=10 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nCaputo was born and raised in [[Hicksville, New York]], on [[Long Island]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pg/TheresaCaputoLongIslandMedium/about/|title=Biography|publisher=Theresa Caputo verified [[Facebook]] page|first=Theresa|last=Caputo|quote=I was born and raised on Long Island in Hicksville, NY.|accessdate=November 14, 2017}}</ref> the daughter of Nicholas and Veronica Brigandi.<ref name=officialbio>{{cite web|url= https://www.theresacaputo.com/about-me/|title=About Me| publisher=Theresa Caputo official website|accessdate=February 27, 2019|quote=My parents Nick and Ronnie...and my brother Michael...}}</ref><ref name=life&style>{{cite news|url= https://www.lifeandstylemag.com/posts/theresa-caputo-mom-and-dad-159097/|title=Theresa Caputo's Mom and Dad Are Also Sad About Her Split From Her Husband Larry|first=Emma|last= Hernandez|work=[[Life & Style]]|date=April 30, 2018|accessdate=February 27, 2019|quote=Theresa's father Nicholas is 77 years old and is from Hicksville, NY which is where he raised Theresa and her brother Michael with his wife, Veronica.}}</ref> She has a brother, Michael.<ref name=officialbio /> Their father was a volunteer firefighter and worked for the Nassau County Department of Public Works until 1980, when he was elected county water commissioner.<ref name=kiwanis>{{cite web|url=http://www.hicksvillekiwanis.org/index.php?page=fmnickb|title=Nicholas J. Brigandi - Spirit of Giving Award|publisher= [[Kiwanis Club]] of Hicksville|date=October 2012|accessdate=February 27, 2019| archivedate= June 23, 2016|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160623223044/http://www.hicksvillekiwanis.org/index.php?page=fmnickb |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nCaputo has been on the [[TLC (TV network)|TLC]] [[reality television|reality]] TV series, ''[[Long Island Medium]]'' since 2011.<ref name=HuffPo-Feature-2015>{{cite news|last1=Cook|first1=Michael|title=\"Long Island Medium\" Theresa Caputo -- \"You Can't Put A Price On What I Am Able To Give People\"|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/michael-cook/long-island-medium-theres_b_8851248.html|accessdate=3 January 2016|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|date=21 December 2015}}</ref> She is also the author of two books and tours under \"Theresa Caputo Live! The Experience\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Keeperman|first1=Brittany|title=Spirited energy: 'Long Island Medium' Theresa Caputo to appear at the Convo|url=http://www.daily-chronicle.com/2016/04/06/spirited-energy-long-island-medium-theresa-caputo-to-appear-at-the-convo/ah878du/|website=[[Daily Chronicle (Illinois)|Daily Chronicle]]|accessdate=7 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Criticism ==\nSeveral people have accused her of being a fraud, ranging from television news programs such as ''[[Inside Edition]]''<ref name=\"insideedition\">{{cite news|title=The Long Island Medium&nbsp;\u2013 Can She Really Communicate with the Dead?|url=http://www.insideedition.com/investigative/5331-the-long-island-medium-can-she-really-communicate-with-the-dead|accessdate=May 21, 2013|work=[[Inside Edition]]|date=August 11, 2012}}</ref><ref name=jezebel-dodai>{{cite news|last=Stewart|first=Dodai|title=Super Sad and Misguided Emails Intended for the Long Island Medium|url=http://jezebel.com/5953012/super-sad-and-misguided-emails-intended-for-the-long-island-medium|accessdate=May 21, 2013|publisher=[[Jezebel (website)|Jezebel.com]]|date=October 20, 2012}}</ref> to print publications such as ''[[Wired Magazine]]''.<ref name=\"wired\">{{cite news |url=https://www.wired.com/underwire/2012/04/opinion_randilimedium0409/ |title=The 'Medium' is not the messenger |magazine=[[Wired Magazine]] |date=2012-04-09 |accessdate=2013-05-19 |last=Randi |first=James |authorlink=James Randi}}</ref> Caputo was described by [[D. J. Grothe]] as a [[charlatan]],<ref name=\"grothe\">{{cite news |last=Grothe |first=DJ |authorlink=D. J. Grothe |title=Priceline.com: Will you prove your spokesperson worthy for a million dollars?|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/dj-grothe/pricelinecom-will-you-pro_b_1773947.html|work=[[The Huffington Post]] |accessdate=2012-08-15}}</ref> and [[James Randi]] said her claims were not true.<ref name=\"wired\" />\n\nIn April 2012, the [[James Randi Educational Foundation]] awarded Caputo its [[Pigasus Award]], a tongue-in-cheek award that seeks to expose [[parapsychology|parapsychological]], [[paranormal]] or [[psychic]] frauds.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KAYG_cgqjWA |title=2012 Pigasus Awards Announcement|work=[[James Randi Educational Foundation]]|date=March 30, 2012|accessdate=March 27, 2014|format=YouTube video}}</ref> The James Randi Education Foundation has been critical of Caputo's work.<ref name=JamesRandi-TallStory-2012>{{cite web|last1=Stollznow|first1=Dr. Karen|authorlink=Karen Stollznow|title=Long Island Medium: A Tall Story|url=http://archive.randi.org/site/index.php/swift-blog/1755-long-island-medium-a-tall-story.html|work=[[James Randi Educational Foundation]]|accessdate=4 January 2016|date=27 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nA newspaper review of Caputo's performances at the [[NYCB Theatre at Westbury]] in late 2017 concluded, \"For me, this unbelievable experience was simply that: not to be believed. In my humble opinion, Caputo is a damn good performer, and she\u2019s got undeniably likable sass and charisma. I just don\u2019t think she speaks with the dead. Or she didn\u2019t the night that I saw her. But my father probably could have told you that.\"<ref>{{cite journal|last=Franchi|first=Jaime|title=My Not-So-Psychic Experience with Long Island Medium Theresa Caputo|url=https://www.longislandpress.com/2014/12/21/my-not-so-psychic-experience-with-long-island-medium-theresa-caputo/|date=December 7, 2014|journal=Long Island Press}}</ref>\n\nParanormal investigator [[Massimo Polidoro]] calls Caputo a \"performer\" and reports on an investigation done by ''[[Inside Edition]]'' and mentalist [[Mark Edward]] who attended one of her live shows in 2012.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Polidoro|first1=Massimo|authorlink=Massimo Polidoro|title=Theresa Caputo: The Fake Long Island Medium|journal=Skeptical Inquirer|date=June 2016|volume=40|issue=3|pages=16\u201317}}</ref> In 2013, illusionist [[Criss Angel]], offered Caputo $1 million to prove her claims.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/criss-angel-on-his-new-show-believe-it-s-healthy-to-be-skeptical-1.6241144|title=Criss Angel on his new show, 'BeLIEve': 'It's healthy' to be skeptical|work=Newsday|location=New York City / Long Island|first=Frank|last=Lovece|authorlink=Frank Lovece|date=October 15, 2013|accessdate=December 7, 2017|quote=\"The Long Island Medium is just another charlatan. Any time she wants, we'll put her through a series of tests and I'll offer a million-dollar challenge to her. And you can put that in black and white.\"}} {{subscription}}</ref>\n\n[[Skeptical movement|Skeptical activist]] [[Susan Gerbic]] has explained several techniques used by Caputo and other psychics, including requiring audience members to log into social media accounts at shows and observing physical identifications such as tattoos.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gerbic|first1=Susan|title=Ten Tricks of the Psychics I Bet You Didn't Know|url=https://www.csicop.org/specialarticles/show/ten_tricks_of_the_psychics_i_bet_you_didnrsquot_know|publisher=Committee for Skeptical Inquiry|accessdate=23 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nOn December 3, 2017, Theresa and her husband Larry Caputo jointly announced they were separating after 28 years of marriage.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/theresa-caputo-splits-husband-long-island-medium/|title=Long Island Medium Theresa Caputo Separates from Husband Larry After 28 Years of Marriage|work=People|first=Stephanie |last=Petit |date=December 3, 2017|accessdate=December 3, 2017}}</ref> They have two children, who have both appeared on the show: Larry Caputo Jr. and Victoria Caputo.<ref name=InkedMag-LarryCaputo-2015>{{cite news|last1=Kovats|first1=Kirstie|title=Larry Caputo Interview: Long Island Medium|url=http://www.inkedmag.com/many-stories-larry-caputo-long-island-medium/|accessdate= January 4, 2016|work=[[Inked Magazine]]|date=4 May 2015}}</ref> On June 27, 2018, Larry Caputo, who moved to Los Angeles following the separation from Theresa, announced he and Theresa were moving from separation to divorce.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2018/06/27/long-island-medium-theresa-larry-caputo-divorce/|title='Long Island Medium' Couple Moving Forward With Divorce|publisher=[[TMZ.com]] |accessdate=July 16, 2018}}</ref> In December 2018, Theresa Caputo announced the divorce had been finalized.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/TheresaCaputoLongIslandMedium/posts/2377400385699340|title=Please read \ud83d\udc95..When Long Island Medium began...|quote= After a year of being separated Larry and I have finalized our divorce.|date=December 18, 2018|publisher=Theresa Caputo verified Facebook page|accessdate=February 27, 2019|archivedate=February 27, 2019| archiveurl=http://archive.is/KJ1pM |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/reality-tv/theresa-larry-caputo-finalize-divorce-1.24714887|title= Theresa and Larry Caputo finalize their divorce|work=[[Newsday]]|location= New York City / Long Island|first=Frank|last= Lovece|authorlink=Frank Lovece|date=December 18, 2018|accessdate=February 27, 2019|quote=Nassau County Supreme Court records show that on Dec. 12, attorneys of the Garden City firm Gassman Biamonte Betts filed a standard Request for Judicial Intervention for plaintiff Theresa R. Caputo in an uncontested divorce from Lawrence P. Caputo. No disposition date is listed in the online record.|archivedate=December 19, 2018|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20181219113340/https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/reality-tv/theresa-larry-caputo-finalize-divorce-1.24714887|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Works and publications ==\n* {{cite book|last1=Caputo|first1=Theresa|last2=Grish|first2=Kristina|title=There's More to Life Than This: Healing Messages, Remarkable Stories, and Insight About the Other Side from the Long Island Medium|date=2013|publisher=Pocket Books|isbn=978-1-4767-2703-5|edition=1st Atria Books hardcover|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781476727035|oclc=872588683|url-access=registration}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Caputo|first1=Theresa|title=You Can't Make This Stuff Up: Life Changing Lessons from Heaven.|date=2014|publisher=Pocket Books|isbn=978-1-4767-6443-6|oclc=903630815}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Caputo|first1=Theresa|title=Good Grief: Heal Your Soul, Honor Your Loved Ones, and Learn to Live Again|date=2017|publisher=Atria Books|isbn= 978-1-5011-3908-6|oclc=956959045}}\n\n==See also==<!-- Please respect alphabetical order -->\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n*[[Ann O'Delia Diss Debar]] (\"One of the most extraordinary fake mediums... the world has ever known\" -Houdini)\n*[[Char Margolis]]\n*''[[Flim-Flam!|Flim-Flam! (Psychics, ESP, Unicorns and other Delusions)]]''\n*[[Fortune telling fraud]]\n*[[Harry Houdini#Debunking spiritualists|Houdini's debunking of psychics and mediums]]\n*[[James Van Praagh]]\n*[[John Edward]]\n*[[Mark Edward]]\n*[[Matt Fraser (psychic)]]\n*''[[Monica the Medium]]''\n*[[Peter Popoff#Investigation by James Randi|Televangelist Peter Popoff exposed by James Randi]]\n*''[[Psychic Blues: Confessions of a Conflicted Medium]]''\n*[[Psychic Friends Network]], telephone psychic service\n*[[Rose Mackenberg]] (Historic investigator of psychic mediums)\n*[[Sylvia Browne]]\n*[[Thomas John Flanagan]]\n*[[Tyler Henry]]\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.theresacaputo.com/}}\n* {{IMDb name|4588554}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Dyball|first1=Rennie|title=Everything You'd Want to Ask the Long Island Medium ... Answered|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20627842,00.html|accessdate=September 10, 2016|work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=September 7, 2012}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caputo, Theresa}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American psychics]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People from Hicksville, New York]]\n[[Category:American spiritual mediums]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "41.81.134.112", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eEarly life:Added content)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theresa_Caputo"}
{"title_page": "Salam Zgharta FC", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date = April 2020}}\n{{short description|Lebanese association football club}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Salam Zgharta\n| image = Logo salam zgharta.png\n| image_size = 200\n| fullname = Salam Zgharta Football Club\n| nickname = \n| short name = Salam, SAL\n| founded = {{Start date and age|15 August 1971}}\n| ground = [[Zgharta Sports Complex]]\n| capacity = 5,500\n| chairman = Estephan Frangieh\n| manager = [[Ghassan Khawaja]]\n| league = {{Lebanese football updater|SAL}}\n| season = {{Lebanese football updater|SAL2}}\n| position = {{Lebanese football updater|SAL3}}\n| website = http://www.salamzgharta.com/\n| pattern_la1=_tri19h\n| pattern_b1=_salam1920h\n| pattern_ra1=_tri19h\n| pattern_sh1=_tri19h\n| pattern_so1=\n| leftarm1=ff0000\n| body1=ff0000\n| rightarm1=ff0000\n| shorts1=ff0000\n| socks1=ff0000\n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2 = \n| pattern_ra2 = \n| pattern_sh2 = \n| pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2 = FFFFFF \n| body2 =  FFFFFF\n| rightarm2 = FFFFFF\n| shorts2 = FFFFFF\n| socks2 = FFFFFF\n}}\n{{Squads sidebar\n|main=Salam Zgharta\n|team1=Salam Zgharta FC\n|league1=Men's\n|team2=Salam Zgharta FC (women)\n|league2=Women's\n}}\n'''Salam Zgharta Football Club''' ({{lang-ar|\u0646\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064a\u0627\u0636\u064a|lit=Zgharta Peace Sporting Club}}), or simply '''Salam''', is a [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] [[association football|football]] [[List of football clubs in Lebanon|club]] based in [[Zgharta]]. Founded in 1971, the club's supporters are mainly from the Zgharta region and other districts in North Lebanon. The club's traditional kit colours are red and black.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.weltfussballarchiv.com/club-profile/lebanon/salam-zgharta-sc/16385/|title=Salam Zgharta SC - Lebanon - \u0646\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064a\u0627\u0636\u064a - Club Profile, Club History, Club Badge, Results, Fixtures, Historical Logos, Statistics|website=www.weltfussballarchiv.com|access-date=16 March 2019}}</ref> In 2014 they won the [[2013\u201314 Lebanese FA Cup|Lebanese FA Cup]], their only major trophy to date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/national/lebanon/lebanon-cup/20132014/s8680/final-stages/|title=Summary - Cup - Lebanon - Results, fixtures, tables and news - Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com|access-date=16 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n=== Early history (1971\u20131990) ===\nSalam Zgharta was founded in 1971, after a group of football enthusiasts bought the licence of former club Salam Achrafieh ({{Lang-ar|\u0646\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0634\u0631\u0641\u064a\u0629}}), based in the [[Achrafieh]] district of [[Beirut]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://al-akhbar.com/Sport_Lebanon/257585|title=\u0645\u0645\u062b\u0651\u0644 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627: \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0634\u0631\u0641\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u062f\u0627\u064a\u0629!|website=\u0627\u0644\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631|language=ar|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> The club's first board of administrators was elected on 15 August 1971, with [[Father Semaan Douaihy]] as the club's honorary president, and [[Youssef Zeidan]] as the executive president.\n\nThe club remained in Achrafieh until 1974, when they moved to [[Zgharta]], in North Lebanon. They competed in the [[Lebanese Premier League]], with [[Sassine Ghazale]] and [[Tannous Al Raheb]] funding the club after the move. During the 1974\u201375 season, [[Antoine Fenianos|Antoine \"Al Shakra\" Fenianos]] was the club's first manager. Salam Zgharta's first game was at the [[Camille Chamoun Sports City Stadium]] against [[Nejmeh SC|Nejmeh]], in which Salam Zgharta lost 5\u20132.\n\nWhile [[football in Lebanon]] was affected by the [[Lebanese Civil War|Civil War]], the [[Lebanese Football Association]] (LFA) split into two entities, with each organizing its own competitions in the latter stage of the war. Salam Zgharta joined the Eastern Federation and won the [[Lebanese FA Cup]] on 12 April 1987, after beating [[Homentmen]] in the final (0\u20130, and 1\u20130 in the replay). However, following the war, the two federations re-merged and the FA Cup win was voided. During the war, Salam Zgharta played against numerous clubs from Syria, Cyprus, and Romania.\n\n=== Post-war period (1990\u20132006) ===\n\nFollowing the end of the Civil War, Salam Zgharta were one of the best teams in the league with a core of good players like [[Fawzi Yammine]], [[Elias Bou Nassif]] and others. The start of the 90's was very good for the northern club, finishing third in the [[1990\u201391 Lebanese Premier League|90\u201391 season]] with 35 points.<ref>https://www.abdogedeon.com/volleyball/NOUJOUM/al%20salam.html</ref> Following the expansion of the [[Lebanese Premier League|Premier League]] to 20 teams divided into two groups, Salam Zgharta finished the [[1991\u201392 Lebanese Premier League|91\u201392 season]] as second of their group and fourth in the league standing after securing 23 points in 20 games.<ref>https://www.abdogedeon.com/volleyball/NOUJOUM/al%20salam.html</ref> The club was able to stay the following two seasons in the top flight but then it struggled to maintain its position in the Lebanese Premier League for financial reasons therefore the club regularly played in the [[Lebanese Second Division]]. In the middle of 1990s, [[Kabalan Yammine]] became the Salam Zgharta's president. In the [[1999\u20132000 Lebanese Premier League|1999\u20132000 season]], Salam Zgharta finished fifth in the Lebanese Premier League, their best result to date. In the mid-2000s Kabalan lost interest in the club; an election took place in October 2006, and [[Estephan Frangieh]] became the president.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n=== Estephan Frangieh's presidency (2006\u2013present) ===\n\nIn the first season under Estephan Frangieh's presidency ([[2006\u201307 Lebanese Premier League|2006\u201307]]), the club was relegated to the Second Division. Following their relegation, Frangieh invested heavily in the club. In 2009 the Merdeshiyeh Stadium was fully renovated, using donations from the fans, and was renamed [[Zgharta Sports Complex]]. Salam Zgharta also established its own academy the same year. Salam Zgharta gained returned to the Premier League in 2008\u201309, but were relegated once again. The club eventually won the [[2012\u201313 Lebanese Second Division]] after topping Group A, gaining promotion to the Premier League.\n\nIn their return to the Premier League in the [[2013\u201314 Lebanese Premier League|2013\u201314 season]], Salam Zgharta hired [[Peter Meindertsma]] as their head coach. While the club struggled to avoid relegation in the league, they won the [[2013\u201314 Lebanese FA Cup]], after beating [[AC Tripoli]] 1\u20130 after extra time in the final. In [[2015 AFC Cup|2015]], Salam Zgharta participated for the first time in the [[AFC Cup]] after winning the one-legged [[2015 AFC Cup qualifying play-off|qualifying play-off round]] match against [[Khayr Vahdat FK|Khayr Vahdat]] 3\u20130 at home. They went on to win one match, against [[Al-Nahda Club (Oman)|Al-Nahda]], in 6 games in the [[2015 AFC Cup group stage|group stage]].\n\nIn the [[2016\u201317 Lebanese Premier League|2016\u201317 season]], Salam Zgharta started the campaign with a 5\u20132 win at home against [[Al Ansar FC|Al Ansar]], the league's record title holders. The season ended with Salam in second position, their best ever finish to date, winning 10 games out of 11 at home. They qualified to the [[2018\u201319 Arab Club Champions Cup]] for the first time, losing 3\u20132 on aggregate against [[Raja Casablanca]] in the round of 32.\n\n==Colors and badges==\nSince the move from [[Achrafieh]] to [[Zgharta]], Salam Zgharta was known for wearing blue at home and white away. After the re-merging of the LFA in 1990, Salam Zgharta opted to change their home colours to red.\n\nThe first ever logo for Salam Zgharta was designed in 1971 by artist [[Pierre Farchakh]]. It consisted of a circle with the words \"Al Salam Zgharta\" ({{Lang-ar|\u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627}}) written in a calligraphic form to take the shape of a pigeon. The design was then changed in 2010, which conserved the round shape. The logo consisted of a circle on top of a bigger circle: the bigger circle was divided in two halves, the top half black with the word \"SALAM\" is written in white, while the bottom half red with the word \"ZGHARTA\" also written in white. The smaller circle was made of a football on top of a pigeon, with red underneath the pigeon. The logo was then re-modernized in 2014.\n\n==Stadium==\nSalam Zgharta owns the [[Zgharta Sports Complex]]. The stadium is located in the Merdeshiyeh region in [[Zgharta]] and currently it can host almost 5500 people. The stadium was built by the maronite endownment next to Sarkis & Bakhos church and it was renovated in 2009 using the donations of the club's fans in Zgharta. In the same year, endownment gave the right of usage of the stadium to Salam Zgharta Club.\nOther than the football pitch, the complex contains an outdoor basketball court, futsal court, headquarters of the club, caferia, gym and a number of studios for the players coming from outside of Zgharta.\n\nThe stadium faced a ban from the federation in 1999\n\n==Supporters==\nSalam Zgharta supporters are mainly located in the [[Zgharta]] and nearby districts. They are known to be passionate even though they are not as numbered as other clubs' fan base. The Salam supporters were known to cause some troubles during matches in the 90's and 00's.\n\n==Club rivalries==\nSalam Zgharta plays the ''[[North Governorate|North]] derby'' with [[AC Tripoli|Tripoli]], as they are both located in the same area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://football-lebanon.com/details.php?id=6664|title=\u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627 \u064a\u062d\u0633\u0645 \u062f\u064a\u0631\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0644 \u0648\u064a\u0636\u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0642\u0627\u0621 \u0641\u064a \u062f\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0636\u0648\u0627\u0621|last=Lebanon|first=Football|website=football-lebanon.com|access-date=13 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reserve team ==\nIn the [[2014\u201315 Lebanese Premier League|2014\u201315 season]], Salam Zgharta's administration bought a [[Lebanese Second Division|Second Division]] club called \"Al Mawada Tripoli\", alongside the contract of [[Mostafa Matar]] and [[Oussama Najjar]], for a fee of $120,000. The club was renamed \"[[Amal Al Salam Zgharta FC|Amal Al Salam Zgharta]]\", and is used as a [[reserve team]] in which all academy graduates play to get experience.\n\nAmal Al Salam Zgharta played in the second division for two seasons in [[2014\u201315 Lebanese Second Division|14\u201315]] and [[2015\u201315 Lebanese Second Division|15\u201316]] and got relegated to the third division.\n\nThis club is not the \"Amal Zgharta Football Club\" which was also the reserve club for Salam Zgharta in the 80's.\n\n==Players==\n===Current squad===\n{{updated|20 April 2020}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.falebanon.com/team/salam-zgharta/|title=Salam Zgharta FC|website=FA Lebanon|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n<!----------------------------- READ THIS NOTICE FIRST BEFORE EDITING ----------------------------------\n \u2013 Do NOT add new players before their signing is officially announced by the club through their website, including medical and signing the contract. A transfer fee agreed doesn't mean the player will sign.\n \u2013 Do NOT remove players before their exit is officially announced by the club.\n \u2013 This is Wikipedia, not a football newspaper. Anything unconfirmed and unsourced will be removed on sight\n  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------>\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1 |nat=LBN|name=[[Mahmoud Saidawi]]|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=2 |nat=LBN|name=[[Hamza Kheir]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=3 |nat=LBN|name=[[Yehya Kahil]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=5 |nat=LBN|name=[[Amer Mahfoud]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=6 |nat=LBN|name=[[Taha Al Hussein]]|pos=FW}} \n{{Fs player|no=7 |nat=LBN|name=[[Jean Jacques Yammine]]|pos=MF|other=[[Captain (association football)|captain]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=9 |nat=LBN|name=[[Hassan Kadi]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|nat=LBN|name=[[Oscar Ghantous]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|nat=LBN|name=[[Imad Karime]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=13|nat=PLE|name=[[Ali Hamam (Palestinian footballer)|Ali Hamam]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=16|nat=LBN|name=[[Ahmad Masri]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|nat=LBN|name=[[Hicham Naboulsi]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=20|nat=LBN|name=[[Walid Fatouh]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|nat=LBN|name=[[Samir Abdulrahman]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=22|nat=LBN|name=[[Hamza El Ali]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=30|nat=LBN|name=[[Ibrahim El Cheikh]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=70|nat=LBN|name=[[Philipe Ayoub]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=95|nat=LBN|name=[[Mostafa Matar]]|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=99|nat=LBN|name=[[Antoine Douaihy (footballer)|Antoine Douaihy]]|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n=== Notable players ===\n{{see also|Category:Salam Zgharta FC players}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n'''Players in international competitions'''\n!Competition\n!Player\n!National team\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[2019 AFC Asian Cup]]\n|[[Walid Ismail]]\n|{{Fb|LIB}}\n|-\n|[[Mostafa Matar]]\n|{{Fb|LIB}}\n|}\n\n==Managerial history==\n<div style=\"font-size:100%\">\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!|Name\n!|Nationality\n!|Years\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Ghassan Khawaja]]{{efn|Caretaker manager|name=caretaker}}\n|{{flagicon|LBN}}\n| align=\"left\" |2009\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Assaf Khalife]]\n|{{flagicon|SYR}}\n| align=\"left\" |2012\u20132013\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Peter Mendeistrama]]\n|{{flagicon|NED}}\n| align=\"left\" |2013\u20132015\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Louai Abou Karam]]\n|{{flagicon|VEN}}\n| align=\"left\" |2015\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Anas Makhlouf]]\n|{{flagicon|SYR}}\n| align=\"left\" |2015\u20132016\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Tarek Jaraya]]\n|{{flagicon|TUN}}\n| align=\"left\" |2016\u20132017\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Maher Sdiri]]\n|{{flagicon|TUN}}\n| align=\"left\" |2017\u20132018\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Tarek Thabet]]\n|{{flagicon|TUN}}\n| align=\"left\" |2018\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Ghassan Khawaja]]\n|{{flagicon|LBN}}\n| align=\"left\" |2018\u20132019\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Anis Boujelban]]{{efn|name=caretaker}}\n|{{flagicon|TUN}}\n| align=\"left\" |2019\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Nouhad Souccar]]\n|{{flagicon|JOR}}\n| align=\"left\" |2019\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Ahmad Kadhem]]\n|{{flagicon|IRQ}}\n| align=\"left\" |2019\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Ghassan Khawaja]]\n|{{flagicon|LBN}}\n| align=\"left\" |2020\u2013present\n|}\n</div>\n\n== Honours ==\n\n* '''[[Lebanese FA Cup]]'''\n**'''Winners (1):''' [[2013\u201314 Lebanese FA Cup|2013\u201314]]\n*'''[[Lebanese Second Division]]'''\n** '''Winners (1):''' 2012\u201313\n*'''[[Lebanese Federation Cup]]'''\n**''Runners-up (1):'' 1999\n*'''[[Lebanese Challenge Cup]]'''\n**''Runners-up (2):'' 2016, [[2019 Lebanese Challenge Cup|2019]]\n\n==Performance in AFC competitions==\n* '''[[AFC Cup]]: 1 appearance'''\n:: [[2015 AFC Cup|2015]]: Group stage\n\n==See also==\n* [[Amal Al Salam Zgharta FC]], reserve team\n* [[Salam Zgharta FC (women)|Salam Zgharta FC Women]], women's team\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://salamzgharta.com}}\n*[http://stats.the-afc.com/tournament/166/teams/1041/profile Salam Zgharta FC] at the [[Asian Football Confederation|AFC]]\n*[https://www.falebanon.com/team/salam-zgharta/ Salam Zgharta FC] at FA Lebanon\n\n{{Lebanese Football League}}\n\n[[Category:Salam Zgharta FC]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Lebanon]]\n[[Category:1971 establishments in Lebanon]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1971]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date = April 2020}}\n{{short description|Lebanese association football club}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Salam Zgharta\n| image = Logo salam zgharta.png\n| image_size = 200\n| fullname = Salam Zgharta Football Club\n| nickname = \n| short name = Salam, SAL\n| founded = {{Start date and age|15 August 1971}}\n| ground = [[Zgharta Sports Complex]]\n| capacity = 5,500\n| chairman = Estephan Frangieh\n| manager = [[Ghassan Khawaja]]\n| league = {{Lebanese football updater|SAL}}\n| season = {{Lebanese football updater|SAL2}}\n| position = {{Lebanese football updater|SAL3}}\n| website = http://www.salamzgharta.com/\n| pattern_la1=_tri19h\n| pattern_b1=_salam1920h\n| pattern_ra1=_tri19h\n| pattern_sh1=_tri19h\n| pattern_so1=\n| leftarm1=ff0000\n| body1=ff0000\n| rightarm1=ff0000\n| shorts1=ff0000\n| socks1=ff0000\n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2 = \n| pattern_ra2 = \n| pattern_sh2 = \n| pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2 = FFFFFF \n| body2 =  FFFFFF\n| rightarm2 = FFFFFF\n| shorts2 = FFFFFF\n| socks2 = FFFFFF\n}}\n{{Squads sidebar\n|main=Salam Zgharta\n|team1=Salam Zgharta FC\n|league1=Men's\n|team2=Salam Zgharta FC (women)\n|league2=Women's\n}}\n'''Salam Zgharta Football Club''' ({{lang-ar|\u0646\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064a\u0627\u0636\u064a|lit=Zgharta Peace Sporting Club}}), or simply '''Salam''', is a [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] [[association football|football]] [[List of football clubs in Lebanon|club]] based in [[Zgharta]]. Founded in 1971, the club's supporters are mainly from the Zgharta region and other districts in North Lebanon. The club's traditional kit colours are red and black.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.weltfussballarchiv.com/club-profile/lebanon/salam-zgharta-sc/16385/|title=Salam Zgharta SC - Lebanon - \u0646\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064a\u0627\u0636\u064a - Club Profile, Club History, Club Badge, Results, Fixtures, Historical Logos, Statistics|website=www.weltfussballarchiv.com|access-date=16 March 2019}}</ref> In 2014 they won the [[2013\u201314 Lebanese FA Cup|Lebanese FA Cup]], their only major trophy to date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/national/lebanon/lebanon-cup/20132014/s8680/final-stages/|title=Summary - Cup - Lebanon - Results, fixtures, tables and news - Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com|access-date=16 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n=== Early history (1971\u20131990) ===\nSalam Zgharta was founded in 1971, after a group of football enthusiasts bought the licence of former club Salam Achrafieh ({{Lang-ar|\u0646\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0634\u0631\u0641\u064a\u0629}}), based in the [[Achrafieh]] district of [[Beirut]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://al-akhbar.com/Sport_Lebanon/257585|title=\u0645\u0645\u062b\u0651\u0644 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627: \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0634\u0631\u0641\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u062f\u0627\u064a\u0629!|website=\u0627\u0644\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631|language=ar|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> The club's first board of administrators was elected on 15 August 1971, with [[Father Semaan Douaihy]] as the club's honorary president, and [[Youssef Zeidan]] as the executive president.\n\nThe club remained in Achrafieh until 1974, when they moved to [[Zgharta]], in North Lebanon. They competed in the [[Lebanese Premier League]], with [[Sassine Ghazale]] and [[Tannous Al Raheb]] funding the club after the move. During the 1974\u201375 season, [[Antoine Fenianos|Antoine \"Al Shakra\" Fenianos]] was the club's first manager. Salam Zgharta's first game was at the [[Camille Chamoun Sports City Stadium]] against [[Nejmeh SC|Nejmeh]], in which Salam Zgharta lost 5\u20132.\n\nWhile [[football in Lebanon]] was affected by the [[Lebanese Civil War|Civil War]], the [[Lebanese Football Association]] (LFA) split into two entities, with each organizing its own competitions in the latter stage of the war. Salam Zgharta joined the Eastern Federation and won the [[Lebanese FA Cup]] on 12 April 1987, after beating [[Homentmen]] in the final (0\u20130, and 1\u20130 in the replay). However, following the war, the two federations re-merged and the FA Cup win was voided. During the war, Salam Zgharta played against numerous clubs from Syria, Cyprus, and Romania.\n\n=== Post-war period (1990\u20132006) ===\n\nFollowing the end of the Civil War, Salam Zgharta were one of the best teams in the league with a core of good players like [[Fawzi Yammine]], [[Elias Bou Nassif]] and others. The start of the 90's was very good for the northern club, finishing third in the [[1990\u201391 Lebanese Premier League|90\u201391 season]] with 35 points.<ref>https://www.abdogedeon.com/volleyball/NOUJOUM/al%20salam.html</ref> Following the expansion of the [[Lebanese Premier League|Premier League]] to 20 teams divided into two groups, Salam Zgharta finished the [[1991\u201392 Lebanese Premier League|91\u201392 season]] as second of their group and fourth in the league standing after securing 23 points in 20 games.<ref>https://www.abdogedeon.com/volleyball/NOUJOUM/al%20salam.html</ref> The club was able to stay the following two seasons in the top flight but then it struggled to maintain its position in the Lebanese Premier League for financial reasons therefore the club regularly played in the [[Lebanese Second Division]]. In the middle of 1990s, [[Kabalan Yammine]] became the Salam Zgharta's president. In the [[1999\u20132000 Lebanese Premier League|1999\u20132000 season]], Salam Zgharta finished fifth in the Lebanese Premier League, their best result to date. In the mid-2000s Kabalan lost interest in the club; an election took place in October 2006, and [[Estephan Frangieh]] became the president.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n=== Estephan Frangieh's presidency (2006\u2013present) ===\n\nIn the first season under Estephan Frangieh's presidency ([[2006\u201307 Lebanese Premier League|2006\u201307]]), the club was relegated to the Second Division. Following their relegation, Frangieh invested heavily in the club. In 2009 the Merdeshiyeh Stadium was fully renovated, using donations from the fans, and was renamed [[Zgharta Sports Complex]]. Salam Zgharta also established its own academy the same year. Salam Zgharta gained returned to the Premier League in 2008\u201309, but were relegated once again. The club eventually won the [[2012\u201313 Lebanese Second Division]] after topping Group A, gaining promotion to the Premier League.\n\nIn their return to the Premier League in the [[2013\u201314 Lebanese Premier League|2013\u201314 season]], Salam Zgharta hired [[Peter Meindertsma]] as their head coach. While the club struggled to avoid relegation in the league, they won the [[2013\u201314 Lebanese FA Cup]], after beating [[AC Tripoli]] 1\u20130 after extra time in the final. In [[2015 AFC Cup|2015]], Salam Zgharta participated for the first time in the [[AFC Cup]] after winning the one-legged [[2015 AFC Cup qualifying play-off|qualifying play-off round]] match against [[Khayr Vahdat FK|Khayr Vahdat]] 3\u20130 at home. They went on to win one match, against [[Al-Nahda Club (Oman)|Al-Nahda]], in 6 games in the [[2015 AFC Cup group stage|group stage]].\n\nIn the [[2016\u201317 Lebanese Premier League|2016\u201317 season]], Salam Zgharta started the campaign with a 5\u20132 win at home against [[Al Ansar FC|Al Ansar]], the league's record title holders. The season ended with Salam in second position, their best ever finish to date, winning 10 games out of 11 at home. They qualified to the [[2018\u201319 Arab Club Champions Cup]] for the first time, losing 3\u20132 on aggregate against [[Raja Casablanca]] in the round of 32.\n\n==Colors and badges==\nSince the move from [[Achrafieh]] to [[Zgharta]], Salam Zgharta was known for wearing blue at home and white away. After the re-merging of the LFA in 1990, Salam Zgharta opted to change their home colours to red.\n\nThe first ever logo for Salam Zgharta was designed in 1971 by artist [[Pierre Farchakh]]. It consisted of a circle with the words \"Al Salam Zgharta\" ({{Lang-ar|\u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627}}) written in a calligraphic form to take the shape of a pigeon. The design was then changed in 2010, which conserved the round shape. The logo consisted of a circle on top of a bigger circle: the bigger circle was divided in two halves, the top half black with the word \"SALAM\" is written in white, while the bottom half red with the word \"ZGHARTA\" also written in white. The smaller circle was made of a football on top of a pigeon, with red underneath the pigeon. The logo was then re-modernized in 2014.\n\n==Stadium==\nSalam Zgharta owns the [[Zgharta Sports Complex]]. The stadium is located in the Merdeshiyeh region in [[Zgharta]] and currently it can host almost 5500 people. The stadium was built by the maronite endownment next to Sarkis & Bakhos church and it was renovated in 2009 using the donations of the club's fans in Zgharta. In the same year, endownment gave the right of usage of the stadium to Salam Zgharta Club.\nOther than the football pitch, the complex contains an outdoor basketball court, futsal court, headquarters of the club, caferia, gym and a number of studios for the players coming from outside of Zgharta.\n\nThe stadium faced a ban from the federation in 1999\n\n==Supporters==\nSalam Zgharta supporters are mainly located in the [[Zgharta]] and nearby districts. They are known to be passionate even though they are not as numbered as other clubs' fan base. The Salam supporters were known to cause some troubles during matches in the 90's and 00's.\n\n==Club rivalries==\nSalam Zgharta plays the ''[[North Governorate|North]] derby'' with [[AC Tripoli|Tripoli]], as they are both located in the same area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://football-lebanon.com/details.php?id=6664|title=\u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0632\u063a\u0631\u062a\u0627 \u064a\u062d\u0633\u0645 \u062f\u064a\u0631\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0644 \u0648\u064a\u0636\u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0642\u0627\u0621 \u0641\u064a \u062f\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0636\u0648\u0627\u0621|last=Lebanon|first=Football|website=football-lebanon.com|access-date=13 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reserve team ==\nIn the [[2014\u201315 Lebanese Premier League|2014\u201315 season]], Salam Zgharta's administration bought a [[Lebanese Second Division|Second Division]] club called \"Al Mawada Tripoli\", alongside the contract of [[Mostafa Matar]] and [[Oussama Najjar]], for a fee of $120,000. The club was renamed \"[[Amal Al Salam Zgharta FC|Amal Al Salam Zgharta]]\", and is used as a [[reserve team]] in which all academy graduates play to get experience.\n\nAmal Al Salam Zgharta played in the second division for two seasons in [[2014\u201315 Lebanese Second Division|14\u201315]] and [[2015\u201315 Lebanese Second Division|15\u201316]] and got relegated to the third division.\n\nThis club is not the \"Amal Zgharta Football Club\" which was the main club in [[Zgharta]] in the 80's.\n\n==Players==\n===Current squad===\n{{updated|20 April 2020}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.falebanon.com/team/salam-zgharta/|title=Salam Zgharta FC|website=FA Lebanon|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n<!----------------------------- READ THIS NOTICE FIRST BEFORE EDITING ----------------------------------\n \u2013 Do NOT add new players before their signing is officially announced by the club through their website, including medical and signing the contract. A transfer fee agreed doesn't mean the 