orse births]]\n[[Category:2012 racehorse deaths]]\n[[Category:Racehorses bred in Australia]]\n[[Category:Racehorses trained in Australia]]\n[[Category:Sydney Cup winners]]\n[[Category:Thoroughbred family 18]]\n", "name_user": "ToddyOC", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eRace record", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tie_the_Knot"}
{"title_page": "Burnett County, Wisconsin", "text_new": "{{Infobox U.S. county\n| county  = Burnett County\n| state = Wisconsin\n| ex image = Burnett County Government Center - 2004.jpg\n| ex image size = 220px\n| ex image cap = [[Burnett County Government Center]]\n| seal =\n| founded year = 1865\n| named for = [[Thomas P. Burnett]]\n| founded date =\n| seat = [[Siren, Wisconsin|Siren]]<ref name=\"seat\">Burnett County Clerk. ''[http://www.burnettcounty.com/documentcenter/view/6164 Burnett County Directory June 2016]''</ref>\n| largest city wl = Grantsburg\n| city type = village\n| area_total_sq_mi = 880\n| area_land_sq_mi = 822\n| area_water_sq_mi = 58\n| area percentage = 6.6\n| population_as_of = 2010\n| population_total = 15457\n| pop_est_as_of = 2018\n| population_est = 15,392\n| population_density_sq_mi = auto\n| web = BurnettCounty.com\n| time zone = Central\n| district = 7th\n}}\n\n'''Burnett County''' is a [[County (United States)|county]] located in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Wisconsin]]. As of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], the population was 15,457.<ref name=\"QF\">{{cite web|title=State & County QuickFacts|url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/55/55013.html|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=January 17, 2014}}</ref> Its [[county seat]] is [[Siren, Wisconsin|Siren]],<ref name=\"seat\"/><ref name=\"seat2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wicounties.org/counties.iml |accessdate=April 22, 2018 |title=The Counties [of Wisconsin]|publisher=Wisconsin Counties Association }}</ref> with the majority of county governmental services located at the [[Burnett County Government Center]]. The county was created in 1856 and organized in 1865.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://publications.newberry.org/ahcbp/documents/WI_Individual_County_Chronologies.htm|title=Wisconsin: Individual County Chronologies|website=Wisconsin Atlas of Historical County Boundaries|publisher=[[Newberry Library|The Newberry Library]]|date=2007|accessdate=August 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:Burnett Co WI Pie Chart No Text Version.pdf|thumb|right|Soils of Burnett County<ref>Nelson, Steven (2011). ''Savanna Soils of Minnesota.'' Minnesota: Self. pp. 61 - 64. {{ISBN|978-0-615-50320-2}}.</ref>]]\n\nAccording to the [[U.S. Census Bureau]], the county has a total area of {{convert|880|sqmi}}, of which {{convert|872|sqmi}} is land and {{convert|58|sqmi}} (6.6%) is water.<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=http://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/counties_list_55.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=August 2, 2015|date=August 22, 2012|title=2010 Census Gazetteer Files}}</ref> Saginaw Lake is located in the county,<ref>http://dnr.wi.gov/lakes/lakepages/LakeDetail.aspx?wbic=2494700 Wisconsin DNR: Saginaw Lake</ref> south of the [[Namekagon River]].\n\n===Adjacent counties===\n* [[Douglas County, Wisconsin|Douglas County]] \u2013 northeast\n* [[Washburn County, Wisconsin|Washburn County]] \u2013 east\n* [[Barron County, Wisconsin|Barron County]] \u2013 southeast\n* [[Polk County, Wisconsin|Polk County]] \u2013 south\n* [[Chisago County, Minnesota]] \u2013 southwest\n* [[Pine County, Minnesota]] \u2013 west\n\n===Major highways===\n* [[Image:WIS 35.svg|20px]] [[Highway 35 (Wisconsin)]]\n* [[Image:WIS 48.svg|20px]] [[Highway 48 (Wisconsin)]]\n* [[Image:WIS 70.svg|20px]] [[Highway 70 (Wisconsin)]]\n* [[Image:WIS 77.svg|20px]] [[Highway 77 (Wisconsin)]]\n* [[Image:WIS 87.svg|20px]] [[Highway 87 (Wisconsin)]]\n\n===Airports===\n* [[Burnett County Airport]] (KRZN) serves the county and surrounding communities.\n* [[Grantsburg Municipal Airport]] (KGTG) enhances county service.\n\n===National protected area===\n* [[Saint Croix National Scenic Riverway]] (part)\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1860= 12\n|1870= 706\n|1880= 3140\n|1890= 4393\n|1900= 7478\n|1910= 9026\n|1920= 10735\n|1930= 10233\n|1940= 11382\n|1950= 10236\n|1960= 9214\n|1970= 9276\n|1980= 12340\n|1990= 13084\n|2000= 15674\n|2010= 15457\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=15392\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=July 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|align-fn=center\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=U.S. Decennial Census|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref><br />1790\u20131960<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mapserver.lib.virginia.edu|title=Historical Census Browser|publisher=University of Virginia Library|accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref> 1900\u20131990<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/cencounts/wi190090.txt|title=Population of Counties by Decennial Census: 1900 to 1990|publisher=United States Census Bureau|editor-last=Forstall|editor-first=Richard L.|date=March 27, 1995|accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref><br />1990\u20132000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/www/cen2000/briefs/phc-t4/tables/tab02.pdf|title=Census 2000 PHC-T-4. Ranking Tables for Counties: 1990 and 2000|publisher=United States Census Bureau|date=April 2, 2001|accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref> 2010\u20132018<ref name=\"QF\"/>\n}}\n{{Stack|[[Image:USA Burnett County, Wisconsin age pyramid.svg|thumb|left|2000 Census Age Pyramid for Burnett County]]}}\n\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name=\"GR8\">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=May 14, 2011 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 15,674 people, 6,613 households, and 4,503 families residing in the county.  The [[population density]] was 19 people per square mile (7/km\u00b2). There were 12,582 housing units at an average density of 15 per square&nbsp;mile (6/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the county was 93.25% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 0.36% [[Race (United States Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 4.45% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 0.24% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 0.07% [[Race (United States Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.21% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.42% from two or more races. 0.77% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race. 28.9% were of [[German people|German]], 15.4% [[Swedish people|Swedish]], 12.8% [[Norwegian people|Norwegian]] and 6.3% [[Irish people|Irish]] ancestry.\n\nThere were 6,613 households out of which 25.10% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 56.20% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 7.50% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.90% were non-families. 26.90% of all households were made up of individuals and 12.20% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.33 and the average family size was 2.80.\n\nIn the county, the population was spread out with 22.10% under the age of 18, 6.00% from 18 to 24, 23.20% from 25 to 44, 28.40% from 45 to 64, and 20.30% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 44 years. For every 100 females there were 101.50 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 100.30 males.\n\nIn 2017, there were 118 births, giving a general fertility rate of 58.5 births per 1000 women aged 15\u201344, the 23rd lowest rate out of all 72 Wisconsin counties.<ref>[https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/publication/p01161-2019-tb.xlsx Annual Wisconsin Birth and Infant Mortality Report, 2017 P-01161-19 (June 2019): Detailed Tables]</ref> Additionally, there were no reported induced abortions performed on women of Burnett County residence in 2017.<ref>[https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/publications/p45360-17.pdf Reported Induced Abortions in Wisconsin], Office of Health Informatics, Division of Public Health, Wisconsin Department of Health Services. Section: Trend Information, 2013-2017, Table 18, pages 17-18</ref>\n{{-}}\n\n==Communities==\nBurnett County is one of only three Wisconsin counties that have no incorporated cities. It is the only Wisconsin county to have villages but no cities.{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n===Villages===\n* [[Grantsburg, Wisconsin|Grantsburg]]\n* [[Siren, Wisconsin|Siren]]\n* [[Webster, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Webster]]\n\n===Towns===\n{{div col|colwidth=12em}}\n* [[Anderson, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Anderson]]\n* [[Blaine, Wisconsin|Blaine]]\n* [[Daniels, Wisconsin|Daniels]]\n* [[Dewey, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Dewey]]\n* [[Grantsburg (town), Wisconsin|Grantsburg]]\n* [[Jackson, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Jackson]]\n* [[La Follette, Wisconsin|La Follette]]\n* [[Lincoln, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Lincoln]]\n* [[Meenon, Wisconsin|Meenon]]\n* [[Oakland, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Oakland]]\n* [[Roosevelt, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Roosevelt]]\n* [[Rusk, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Rusk]]\n* [[Sand Lake, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Sand Lake]]\n* [[Scott, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Scott]]\n* [[Siren (town), Wisconsin|Siren]]\n* [[Swiss, Wisconsin|Swiss]]\n* [[Trade Lake, Wisconsin|Trade Lake]]\n* [[Union, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Union]]\n* [[Webb Lake, Wisconsin|Webb Lake]]\n* [[West Marshland, Wisconsin|West Marshland]]\n* [[Wood River, Wisconsin|Wood River]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Census-designated place===\n* [[Danbury, Wisconsin|Danbury]]\n\n===Unincorporated communities===\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n* [[Alpha, Wisconsin|Alpha]]\n* [[Bashaw, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Bashaw]]\n* [[Benson, Wisconsin|Benson]]\n* [[Branstad, Wisconsin|Branstad]]\n* [[Coomer, Wisconsin|Coomer]]\n* [[Falun, Wisconsin|Falun]]\n* [[Four Corners, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Four Corners]]\n* [[Gaslyn, Wisconsin|Gaslyn]]\n* [[Hertel, Wisconsin|Hertel]]\n* [[Lind, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Lind]]\n* [[Oakland (community), Burnett County, Wisconsin|Oakland]]\n* [[Pole Cat Crossing, Wisconsin|Pole Cat Crossing]] (partial)\n* [[Randall, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Randall]]\n* [[Riverside, Burnett County, Wisconsin|Riverside]]\n* [[Timberland, Wisconsin|Timberland]]\n* [[Trade Lake (community), Wisconsin|Trade Lake]]\n* [[Trade River, Wisconsin|Trade River]]\n* [[Webb Lake (community), Wisconsin|Webb Lake]]\n* [[Woodland Corner, Wisconsin|Woodland Corner]]\n* [[Yellow Lake, Wisconsin|Yellow Lake]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Politics==\n{{Hidden begin\n|titlestyle = background:#ccccff;\n|title      = Presidential elections results\n}}\n{| align=\"center\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"float:right; left: 1em 1em 1em 0; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+ '''Presidential elections results'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS|title=Dave Leip's Atlas of U.S. Presidential Elections|first=David|last=Leip|date=|website=uselectionatlas.org|accessdate=April 12, 2018}}</ref>\n|- bgcolor=lightgrey\n! Year\n! [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n! [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n! [[Third Party (United States)|Third parties]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''[[United States presidential election in Wisconsin, 2016|2016]]'''\n|  style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''61.9%''' ''5,410''\n|  style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|33.8% ''2,949''\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|4.3% ''379''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''[[United States presidential election in Wisconsin, 2012|2012]]'''\n|  style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''52.4%''' ''4,550''\n|  style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|45.9% ''3,986''\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|1.6% ''141''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''[[United States presidential election in Wisconsin, 2008|2008]]'''\n|  style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/R